        ]
      },
      "text": [
        " اللَّهِ عَزَّ وَ جَلَّ وَ ما يُؤْمِنُ أَكْثَرُهُمْ بِاللَّهِ إِلَّا وَ هُمْ مُشْرِكُونَ قَالَ يُطِيعُ الشَّيْطَانَ مِنْ حَيْثُ لَا يَعْلَمُ فَيُشْرِكُ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "A number of our companions, from Sahl Bin Ziyad, from Yahya Bin Al Mubarak, from Abdullah Bin Jabala, from Sama’at, from Abu Baseer and Is’haq Bin Ammar, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> regarding the Words of Allah<sup>azwj</sup> Mighty and Majestic <span class=\"ibTxt\"><a href=\"/#/books/quran:12#h106\"><a href=\"/books/quran:12#h106\">[12:106]</a></a> And most of them do not believe in Allah except they are associating others (with Him)</span>. He<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘He obeys the Satan<sup>la</sup> from where he does not even know, so he associates (commits <span class=\"iTxt\">Shirk</span>)’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "3. A number of our people have narrated from Sahl ibn Ziyad from Yahya ibn al- Mubarak from ‘Abd Allah ibn Jabalah from Sama’a from abu Basir and Ishaq ibn ‘Ammar from abu ‘Abd Allah (a.s.) who has said the following: “About the words of Allah, the Most Majestic, the Most Holy, ‘Most of them do not believe in Allah; they are but pagans,’ <a href=\"/#/books/quran:12#h106\"><a href=\"/books/quran:12#h106\">[12:106]</a></a> the Imam said, ‘They obey Satan without realizing it and so they grow to be pagans.’” "
        ]
      }
    },
